<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Akshay M</title><link>https://akshayxml.com/</link><description>Recent content on Akshay M</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://akshayxml.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>About</title><link>https://akshayxml.com/about/</link><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://akshayxml.com/about/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m currently part of the Google Distributed Cloud Air-Gapped team, contributing to the DNS infrastructure. Prior to joining Google, I acquired over 2 years of hands-on experience as a Software Development Engineer at Media.net, building a solid foundation in software development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My journey in tech started with a Master&amp;rsquo;s degree in Computer Science and Engineering from IIIT Hyderabad where I developed my technological abilities as well as established an interest for development. During my college days, I also had the opportunity to work on research internships at Samsung Research Institute and IIST Trivandrum.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Experience</title><link>https://akshayxml.com/experience/</link><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://akshayxml.com/experience/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Here is a summary of my professional work experience.&lt;/p&gt;
